'We agreed that we would all be signatories on the final contract and then they sent us a draft of the agreement and it excluded us,' Arum said.

Not being a signatory would mean that Top Rank wouldn't have control of decisions such as video content and music during the fight.

'They don't want us to have any say,' Arum added. 'That's what we're enmeshed in.'

