Mayweather Promotions CEO Leonard Ellerbe said that Arum 'isn't willing to live with the agreement'

But Leonard Ellerbe, CEO of Mayweather Promotions, disagreed with Arum.

He said: 'The bottom line is that Bob isn't willing to live with the agreement signed a couple months ago, which doesn't allow him to be in control.

'The only conspiracy, in my opinion, exists with him trying to conspire with his lawyers to change the terms of the agreement. I assure you that nothing underhanded is going on and the reference to this back alley stuff is ridiculous.'

